race.comment: WILLINGLY (3) wasn't far away when resuming here over 1200m after she got a long way back in the run. Won here at her only start over this longer sprint and the step up suits now. The premier jockey has won on the mare, and he's reunited. Tough to roll. GEE GEES ME BOY (1) returned from a spell four weeks ago and didn't have the best of it beaten 3.5L. Darmanin switches to the above but he maps well and has plenty up his sleeve. BAYBOUGG (5) improved last time in the WILLINGLY race. Byrne Burke is a positive jockey engagement and she'd be in the finish if she found her best. NO ACCESS (4) turned in a better run last start, beaten just 0.9L into fourth over 1400m at this track. Maps well and has the blinkers applied again. In the mix.
